# Project Context

You are working on Ring - Battle Royale, a top-down multiplayer stick-figure arena game built with Node.js, vanilla JS client, and HTML5 Canvas. Your task is to add NPC bots that automatically fill matches when there are insufficient real players.

## Tech Stack
- Node.js with `ws@^8.16.0` for WebSocket
- Vanilla JS client with HTML5 Canvas (no framework)
- HiDPI-aware rendering: canvas uses `devicePixelRatio` scaling via `ctx.setTransform(dpr, 0, 0, dpr, 0, 0)`, all drawing is in CSS pixels
- Custom test harness — `npm test` runs `node test/game.test.js` (server-side only, currently 877 tests all passing)
- CJS modules (`require` / `module.exports`), `'use strict'` at top of every JS file

## Conventions
- `'use strict'` at top of each JS file
- CSS is inline in `client/index.html` `<style>` block (no external stylesheets)
- Dark theme: backgrounds `#111`/`#1a1a2e`, accent `#4fc`, text `#eee`
- All absolute-positioned UI elements use `z-index: 10` to stay above canvas
- Player objects have shape: `{ id, ws, x, y, angle, hp, alive, lastShot, input: {up,down,left,right}, name }`
- Game states: `'lobby'`, `'active'`, `'round_end'`
- Constants defined at top of `server/game.js`: `ARENA_RADIUS=500`, `PLAYER_RADIUS=15`, `PLAYER_SPEED=200`, `BULLET_SPEED=600`, `PLAYER_MAX_HP=100`, etc.
- Arena is a convex polygon (5-10 vertices), ring shrinks toward centroid over 75s
- `MIN_PLAYERS_TO_START = 2` triggers lobby countdown

## Architecture Overview

The game has a single `Game` class in `server/game.js` that manages all state:
- `this.players` = `Map<id, Player>` — all players (real WebSocket-connected)
- `this.spectators` = `Set<id>` — players who joined mid-match
- `this.bullets` = array of bullet objects
- Game loop: `tick()` called every 50ms (20 Hz), dispatches to `tickLobby()`, `tickActive()`, or `tickRoundEnd()`
- `tickActive()` calls: ring shrink → `movePlayer()` for each alive player → `updateBullets()` → `applyRingDamage()` → `checkWinCondition()`
- `movePlayer(player, dt)` reads `player.input.{up,down,left,right}` to compute movement, clamps to arena polygon
- `tryShoot(player)` creates a bullet if cooldown has elapsed
- `getState(forPlayerId)` serializes full game state for broadcast to clients
- `broadcast()` calls `this.onBroadcast` callback, which the WebSocket server in `index.js` uses to send state to all connected clients

The WebSocket server in `server/index.js`:
- Creates HTTP server serving static files from `client/`
- On WebSocket connect: calls `game.addPlayer(ws)`, sends welcome message
- On message: handles `type: 'input'` (movement/shoot) and `type: 'set_name'` (nickname)
- On disconnect: calls `game.removePlayer(id)`

The client in `client/client.js`:
- Connects via WebSocket, receives state updates at 20 Hz
- Renders with HTML5 Canvas: arena polygon, ring, grid, bullets, stick figures
- `drawStickFigure(player, scale, cx, cy)` renders each player with head, body, legs, arms/weapon, HP bar, name label
- Name label rendering (lines 373-377): uses `player.name` with color `isMe ? '#4fc' : '#aaa'`
- HUD shows game state info, player counts

