```

The `Game` class will call `updateNPCAI(npc, { ... })` passing everything the AI needs.

**AI Behavior (updateNPCAI)**:
1. Check if NPC is outside ring polygon → set movement inputs toward centroid
2. Find nearest alive enemy player (real or NPC, excluding self)
3. If enemy within NPC_SHOOT_RANGE:
   - Compute angle to enemy, set `npc.angle`
   - If angle difference < NPC_AIM_TOLERANCE, return `{ shoot: true }`
   - Set movement inputs to approach enemy
4. If no nearby enemy:
   - Move toward centroid with some randomness (change wander direction every ~2s)
5. Return `{ shoot: boolean }` so the Game can call `tryShoot()`

